In a message dated 12/6/99 6:08:10 PM, Unschooling-dotcom@onelist.com writes:

<<My youngest dd is interested in Russia and is interested in paper dolls or
coloring pages with traditional costumes. does anyone know of any sources?

>>

Dover Press (or is it Dover Publications) does lots of high-quality coloring
books and paper dolls on historical and cultural subjects. I would start
there. Their prices are very reasonable.

Betsy
